<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Welcome to another installment of <em>This Week in Spring!</em> This week <a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/speakers#Josh_Long">I am at DevNexus in Atlanta, GA</a> along with a handful of Spring team members and Spring community luminaries. I’ll be presenting a talk on getting started <a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/speakers#Josh_Long">with Spring Boot</a> and I hope you’ll join me, or one of the many other talks on Spring team:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4156">Spring 4 Web Applications</a> by Rossen Stoyanchev</li>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4446">Cloud Native Apps with Spring Cloud</a> by Spencer Gibb</li>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4765">Building microservices with Scala, functional domain models and Spring Boot</a> by Chris Richardson</li>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4227">What is new in Spring Integration 4?</a> by Marius Bogoevici</li>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4417">Spring Data REST - Data Meets Hypermedia</a> by Greg Turnquist and Roy Clarkson</li>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4444">IoT Realized - The Connected Car</a> by Michael Minella</li>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4409">Keeping It Clean - Lessons learned from Open Source on how to polish code</a> by Phillip Webb</li>
<li><a href="https://devnexus.com/s/devnexus2015/presentations#id-4448">Spring Integration Java DSL - A Deep Dive</a> by Gary Russell</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
